	<preparation>Hydrate the saffron in 3 Tbl hot water.  Salt the eggplant and leave to drain in a colander for 30 minutes before rinsing and drying.  In a large frying pan heat oil and fry onion, garlic and peppers and eggplant for about 5 minutes. 

Stir occasionally.  Add paprika and thence the rice, stock, tomatoes, saffron and salt and pepper to taste.  Bring to a boil and reduce to simmer for 15 minutes uncovered, stirring occasionally and shaking the pan frequently.</preparation>
